        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                <p>Assuming that you are using Ubuntu guest in your VirtualBox, and you are using NAT as the network mode.</p>
<p><strong>Step 1, install and configure openssh-server:</strong></p>
<div class="highlight">
<pre><code>sudo apt install openssh-server
</code></pre>
</div>
<p><strong>Step 2, setup port fowarding in VirtualBox In VirtualBox</strong></p>
<p>Right click your Virtual Machine (eg. Ubuntu), go to <code>Network</code> -&gt; <code>Advanced</code> -&gt; <code>Port forwarding</code>, add a new entry like below:</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 109.484%; height: 61px;" border="1">
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 51px;">
<td style="width: 16.6667%; height: 51px;"><span style="color: #2dc26b;"><strong>Name</strong></span></td>
<td style="width: 16.6667%; height: 51px;"><span style="color: #2dc26b;"><strong>Protocol</strong></span></td>
<td style="width: 16.6667%; height: 51px;"><span style="color: #2dc26b;"><strong>Host IP</strong></span></td>
<td style="width: 16.6667%; height: 51px;"><span style="color: #2dc26b;"><strong>Host Port</strong></span></td>
<td style="width: 16.6667%; height: 51px;"><span style="color: #2dc26b;"><strong>Guest IP</strong></span></td>
<td style="width: 20.9164%; height: 51px;"><span style="color: #2dc26b;"><strong>Guest Port</strong></span></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 10px;">
<td style="width: 16.6667%; height: 10px;">SSH</td>
<td style="width: 16.6667%; height: 10px;">TCP</td>
<td style="width: 16.6667%; height: 10px;"> </td>
<td style="width: 16.6667%; height: 10px;">2222</td>
<td style="width: 16.6667%; height: 10px;"> </td>
<td style="width: 20.9164%; height: 10px;">22</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<figure class="post__image post__image--center"><img loading="lazy"  src="file:///C:/Users/ben/Documents/Publii/sites/bens-blog/preview/media/posts/1/ssh-port-fowarding.png" sizes="(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 768px" srcset="file:///C:/Users/ben/Documents/Publii/sites/bens-blog/preview/media/posts/1/responsive/ssh-port-fowarding-xs.png 300w ,file:///C:/Users/ben/Documents/Publii/sites/bens-blog/preview/media/posts/1/responsive/ssh-port-fowarding-sm.png 480w ,file:///C:/Users/ben/Documents/Publii/sites/bens-blog/preview/media/posts/1/responsive/ssh-port-fowarding-md.png 768w ,file:///C:/Users/ben/Documents/Publii/sites/bens-blog/preview/media/posts/1/responsive/ssh-port-fowarding-lg.png 1024w ,file:///C:/Users/ben/Documents/Publii/sites/bens-blog/preview/media/posts/1/responsive/ssh-port-fowarding-xl.png 1360w ,file:///C:/Users/ben/Documents/Publii/sites/bens-blog/preview/media/posts/1/responsive/ssh-port-fowarding-2xl.png 1600w"  alt="NATPortForward" width="780" height="350"></figure>
<p><strong>Step 3, SSH to Ubuntu in your Host OS</strong></p>
<div class="highlight">
<pre><code><span class="c1"># Change &lt;username&gt; to your Ubuntu login name, and input password when it prompts</span>
ssh -l &lt;username&gt; <span class="m">127</span>.0.0.1 -p <span class="m">2222</span> 
</code></pre>
</div>
